# Repo context budget

Follow [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) § Context loading. Do not preload planning docs.

## Doc boundaries

| Load | When |
|------|------|
| `AGENTS.md`, `docs/phase4-implementation-spec.md` | Always (once per session) |
| `docs/phase3-implementation-spec.md` | Phase 3 maintenance only |
| `docs/phase2-implementation-spec.md` | Phase 2 maintenance only |
| `services/state-service/AGENTS.md` | Go State Service work |
| `services/alert-service/AGENTS.md` | Go Alert Service work |
| `services/graph-service/AGENTS.md`, `services/simulation-service/AGENTS.md` | Phase 4 graph/simulation work |
| `docs/data-flow.md` | Envelope, idempotency, or outbox tasks only |
| `docs/architecture.md`, `domain-model.md`, `compliance-mapping.md`, `roadmap.md`, ADRs (except ADR-007) | Only when task explicitly requires |

## Verification mode

If the task is smoke test, integration verify, or `/verify-phase2`:

1. Run `./scripts/smoke-test.sh` and `./scripts/smoke-test-phase2.sh` before any Read of prior sessions
2. Load only `AGENTS.md` + relevant service `AGENTS.md`
3. See [docs/handoff-verification-agent.md](../docs/handoff-verification-agent.md)

Phase 4 integration: `./scripts/smoke-test-phase4.sh` when graph/simulation stack is in scope.

## Do not read (implementation / verification)

Unless the user pasted a path for scoring:

- `~/.cursor/projects/**/agent-transcripts/**`
- `~/.cursor/projects/**/terminals/**` (use `Await` once; no double-Read)
- `evals/harness/`, `evals/fixtures/` — scoring answer keys during live evals
- `evals/live-model/README.md`, `evals/live-model/manifest.json` — run scripts instead

## Do not re-read (same session)

Unless the user edited the file, you StrReplace'd it, or the task is harness/meta work:

- **Global:** `~/.cursor/HARNESS.md`, `~/.cursor/TOOLING.md`, `~/.cursor/memory/MEMORY.md`, `~/.cursor/rules/`, `~/.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md`
- **Repo contract:** `AGENTS.md`, phase specs, `docs/handoff-parallel-agent.md`, `docs/handoff-verification-agent.md`
- **Eval harness:** `scripts/score-agent-transcript.py`, eval README/manifest — run scripts instead of reading source

For `/token-efficiency`, `/live-eval`, and `/live-eval-phase2`: one Shell call to `./scripts/token-efficiency.sh`, `./scripts/run-live-evals.sh`, or `./scripts/run-live-evals-phase2.sh`; no Read of scorer/eval files.

## Relevant skills (prefer these)

- `verifying-changes`, `systematic-debugging`, `planning-implementations`
- `agent-worktrees` (global — worktree / best-of-N patterns; repo scripts under `scripts/agent-worktree*.sh`)
- `docker-expert` (Compose/stack tasks)
- `capturing-learnings` (repo gotchas → AGENTS.md, not global memory)

Skip `dispatching-parallel-agents` unless the user asks about parallelization effectiveness.

## Parallel / worktree rules (load on demand)

- Global: `22-parallel-agents.mdc` when orchestrating parallel agents or best-of-N
- Repo: `worktrees-repo.mdc` when creating worktrees or acting as parent/child in this stack
- Parent merge/smoke: `/parallel-parent` or [handoff-parallel-parent.md](../docs/handoff-parallel-parent.md)

## Ignore unless asked

Prisma, Vercel, Encore, Neon, and other full-stack plugin skills unrelated to this stack. UI-only skills unless working on `apps/alert-console/`, `apps/audit-explorer/`, `apps/graph-explorer/`, or `apps/simulation-console/`.
